#: 48444
msgid ""
"This tall, thin man, dressed in heavy crimson robes, has sharp, pinched "
"features. He bows regally as you approach him. \"I am Salabesh, oft-called "
"Salabesh the Onyx, future mage-tutor for the Civic Festhall. You've business "
"with me, I take it...?\""
msgstr ""

#: 48445
msgid "\"No... just some questions...\""
msgstr ""

#: 48446
msgid "\"No, I don't. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 48447
msgid ""
"\"About what, hmmm? Not the Ward and the like, I hope... plenty of more "
"common folk could answer such questions, and I'd just as soon direct you to "
"one of them.\""
msgstr ""

#: 48448 48454
msgid "\"Why are you called 'the Onyx?'\""
msgstr ""

#: 48449 48455
msgid "\"What did you mean by 'future mage-tutor of the Festhall?\""
msgstr ""

#: 48450 48456
msgid ""
"\"You're a Master of Curses? Perhaps you could - *hiccup!* - help me...\""
msgstr ""

#: 48451 48457
msgid "\"Are you the mage that cursed the performer down the street?\""
msgstr ""

#: 48452 48458
msgid "\"Never mind. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 48453
msgid "Salabesh smirks. \"I am not surprised.\""
msgstr ""

#: 48459
msgid ""
"\"A long tale, which I'll shorten to save my breath. In my youth, I was once "
"called Salabesh the Golden, for I was said to have a heart of gold... small, "
"hard and yellow. Well, I cursed the fool who started *that* so that he could "
"only speak from his arse and defecate through his mouth. The 'Onyx' "
"appellation - along the same lines as 'the Golden,' though admittedly "
"somewhat less clever - soon followed. In any case, I'm a much kinder fellow "
"now... far less prone to laying curses and the like. I'm not certain if I "
"deserve the name any longer.\""
msgstr ""

#: 48460 48490 48494 48498 66238 66243 66245 67853
msgid "\"I had another question...\""
msgstr ""

#: 48461 48491 48495 48499 66239 66244 66246 67854 67857
msgid "\"That's all I wished to know. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 48462
msgid ""
"\"Help you?\" Salabesh sneers. \"Doubtful.\" Before you can respond, he "
"sighs, shaking his head. \"Well... *perhaps* I could. What troubles you, "
"then?\""
msgstr ""

#: 48463
msgid "\"Jumble Murdersense cursed me.\""
msgstr ""

#: 48464
msgid "\"Never mind, actually. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 48465
msgid ""
"\"Jumble Murdersense? Hah! That sputtering mooncalf could *never* best me! "
"Oh, the battles we used to have, though...\" Salabesh frowns. \"But I'm past "
"all that, now. No longer my sort of thing, you see. I really don't know what "
"I could do for you... after all, it's *his* curse. Not the sort you'd find "
"on an item or somesuch, you know, that you could remove with simple "
"magicks... *he'll* have to remove it, and willingly.\""
msgstr ""

#: 48466
msgid "\"Well, could you teach me a curse, then, that I could use on him?\""
msgstr ""

#: 48467 48472 67856
msgid "\"I had another question, then...\""
msgstr ""

#: 48468 48473
msgid "\"In that case, farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 48469
msgid ""
"\"Hmm. Well... I don't normally do that. I keep my curses to myself, you "
"know. And besides, even a single curse would take one a long, long while to "
"learn - more time than I'd care to spend on it.\""
msgstr ""

#: 48470
msgid "\"I could pay you for your trouble...\""
msgstr ""

#: 48471 48475
msgid ""
"\"Perhaps you're just worried your curses aren't good enough to best him, "
"anymore...\""
msgstr ""

#: 48474
msgid ""
"\"No, no... I've simply no desire to do it.\" Salabesh looks directly into "
"your eyes. \"Now kindly drop the subject, sirrah, before you begin to annoy "
"me.\""
msgstr ""

#: 48476
msgid "\"All right. I had another question...\""
msgstr ""

#: 48477
msgid "\"It's dropped, Salabesh. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 48478
msgid ""
"\"You *what?!* Of all the ridiculous... now look here, you knuckle-dragging "
"sack of scars, Salabesh the Onyx is the *MASTER* of Curses, and there is no "
"other! Why, I could give you but a single phrase that would render that "
"nincompoop's cursing wholly impotent!\""
msgstr ""

#: 48479
msgid "\"Teach it to me, then...\""
msgstr ""

#: 48480
msgid "Purse your lips, look skeptical."
msgstr ""

#: 48481
msgid "\"I'm sure you could. I had another question...\""
msgstr ""

#: 48484
msgid "\"All right, all right... farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 48485
msgid ""
"\"That's it! You've *made* me do it!\" Salabesh utters a short string of "
"impossible syllables... words of power, which you note mentally for later "
"use against Jumble. \"There! See what *that* does to him, and tell me "
"Salabesh the Onyx isn't *the* Master of Curses, then!\""
msgstr ""

#: 48486
msgid "\"Thanks, Salabesh; I'll do that. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 48487
msgid ""
"I learned a short curse from Salabesh the Onyx, which I should be able to "
"use against Jumble Murdersense."
msgstr ""

#: 48488
msgid ""
"\"Oh...\" Salabesh narrows his eyes; his lip curls up. \"*Him.* Yes, I "
"cursed him, and he was well-deserving of it! Mocking a passing mage... now "
"what sort of fool does that? He was *asking* for it! After all, I *am* "
"Salabesh the Onyx, Master of Curses. Don't worry yourself, though... the "
"curse is harmless. Improves his sorry little act, if anything - he'll be "
"fine.\""
msgstr ""

#: 48489 66237
msgid "\"Master of Curses? Perhaps you could - *hiccup!* - help me, then...\""
msgstr ""

#: 48492
msgid ""
"\"It's a prestigious position, to be an official tutor in one the Festhall's "
"training chambers. It's my intention to one day take the position of mages' "
"tutor, but the title's currently in the possession of the Lady Thorncombe. "
"If only I could somehow prove that I'd be a superior tutor...\""
msgstr ""

#: 48493
msgid ""
"\"You could always bring up the fact that she's addicted to sensory stones. "
"She doesn't seem to want to teach anymore...\""
msgstr ""

#: 48496
msgid ""
"I told Salabesh that Lady Thorncombe spent all her time in the sensorium and "
"no longer wished to teach. He was eager to take up her position himself, but "
"I'm unsure as to how good a tutor he'd be. Perhaps I'd best inform Lady "
"Thorncombe of his intentions to give her a final chance to sort out her "
"priorities."
msgstr ""

#: 48497
msgid ""
"Salabesh's tight lips curl into a nasty smile. \"*Is* she, now? And she no "
"longer cares to teach? Excellent...\" He rubs his hands together, like a "
"clich' villain with a dastardly plot. \"I'll request to be made the new "
"mage's tutor shortly, then.\""
msgstr ""

#: 48500
msgid ""
"You see Salabesh the Onyx. He makes a brief but graceful half-bow. \"Hmm. "
"Again you stand before me...\""
msgstr ""

#: 48501
msgid "\"Yes. I had some questions...\""
msgstr ""

#: 48502
msgid "\"I was just passing by. Farewell.\""
msgstr ""

#: 66221
msgid ""
"I met a man named Salabesh outside the Civic Festhall. He claimed to be "
"vying for the prestigious position of 'mage-tutor of the Festhall,' but "
"needs a way to prove that he'd be a better tutor than the current one."
msgstr ""

#: 66236
msgid ""
"\"Oh, yes... you heard right.\" Salabesh sighs happily and chuckles to "
"himself. \"That sort of thing is why I'm know as the Master of Curses, you "
"know.\""
msgstr ""

#: 66240
msgid ""
"\"Reek...? Hmmm.\" Salabesh's eyebrows suddenly dart up. \"Oh, yes... Jumble "
"Murdersense cursed that man, if I recall correctly. Why? Seeking to get his "
"curse undone? Good luck... only Jumble can do that, you know.\""
msgstr ""

#: 66241
msgid "\"Where would I find this Jumble Murdersense?\""
msgstr ""

#: 66242
msgid ""
"\"Within the Civic Festhall, I suppose. A short, portly fellow with a "
"leering smile. Never speaks, so you'll be hard pressed to get anything out "
"of him.\""
msgstr ""

#: 66247 66249
msgid "\"Do you know of a cursed man called Reekwind?\""
msgstr ""

#: 66248
msgid ""
"I was told that Jumble Murdersense made Reekwind - the cursed, stench-ridden "
"man I met in the Hive - what he is, and that I could find him in the Civic "
"Festhall."
msgstr ""

#: 66250
msgid "\"You cursed him so that *what?*\""
msgstr ""

#: 67852
msgid ""
"Salabesh's expression darkens. \"No... I recently upset the head of the "
"Festhall's board of mages, and I feel it would be best to wait for a time "
"before making my request. Besides, I am certain that 'Lady' Thorncombe won't "
"come skipping out of the sensorium anytime soon...\" He chuckles evilly."
msgstr ""

#: 67855
msgid ""
"\"Humph! That vacuous, scatter-brained child of a woman... Thorncombe "
"finally saw fit to leave the sensoriums and return to teaching, so my chance "
"is lost. I do not wish to speak of it any longer!\" Salabesh continues to "
"mumble foul curses beneath his breath."
msgstr ""

#: 67858 67860
msgid ""
"\"Have you put in your request to be made mage-tutor of the Festhall, yet?\""
msgstr ""

#: 67859 67861
msgid ""
"\"So... whatever happened to your becoming mage-tutor of the Festhall?\""
msgstr ""
